\v 11 Then Balak said, “What have you done to me [RHQ]? I brought you here to curse my enemies, but instead you have ◄blessed them/asked Yahweh to bless them►!”
\p
\v 12 But Balaam replied, “I can [RHQ] say only what Yahweh tells me to say. I cannot say anything else.”
\s1 Balaam prophesied about the Israelis again
\p
\v 13 Then King Balak told Balaam, “Come with me to another place. There you will see only part of the Israeli people, and you will be able to curse those people for me.”
\v 14 So Balak took Balaam to a field on the top of Pisgah Mountain. There, again he built seven altars and offered a youngbull and a ram \add as a sacrifice\add* on each altar.
\p
\v 15 Then Balaam said to the king, “Stand here close to your burned offerings, while I go and talk with Yahweh.”
\p
\v 16 So Balaam did that, and Yahweh appeared to Balaam again and gave him another message. Then he said, “Go back to Balak and tell him that message.”
\p
\v 17 So Balaam returned to where the king and the leaders from Moab were standing, next to the altar where Balak had burned the sacrifices. Balak asked him, “What did Yahweh say?”
\p
\v 18 Then Balaam told him this message:
\q1 “Balak, listen carefully;
